NAME
     bsp_nprocs - determine the total number of BSP processes.


C SYNOPSIS
     #include "bsp.h"

     int bsp_nprocs();

FORTRAN SYNOPSIS
     INCLUDE 'fbsp.h'

     INTEGER FUNCTION bspnprocs()


DESCRIPTION
     If the function bsp_nprocs is  called  before  bsp_begin(3),
     then  it  returns  the  total processors which are available
     online. If it is called after bsp_begin(3) it returns _n, the
     actual number of processes allocated to the program, where _1
     <= _n <= _m_a_x_p_r_o_c_s, and _m_a_x_p_r_o_c_s is the  number  of  processes
     requested in bsp_begin(3).


